jackson stayed at the hotel for two weeks as he rehearsed for his national concert tour, which began this week in kansas city, mo
david merrick, the impresario behind some of broadway's biggest hits, is returning to theater production in london in may with an australian comedy, ``emerald city.''
the play by david williamson, who also wrote ``sons of cain,'' opens may 9 at lyric theater, merrick's publicists announced friday
it will be merrick's second production in london, where his long-running musical ``42nd street'' opened in 1984
merrick plans to bring ``emerald city,'' a comedy about domestic rivalry that he first saw last november at the sydney opera house, to london with its australian cast intact
merrick's last broadway production, a 1986 revival of joe orton's ``loot,'' was a financial failure but a critical success. among the biggest hits of his new york career were the musicals ``gypsy'' and ``hello, dolly'' and woody allen's comedy ``play it again sam.''
