rebels also stormed a hospital in the northern luzon province of cagayan and carted off medicine, food and other supplies, military officials said. one civilian was wounded in the raid
the government-run philippine news agency said an undetermined number of new people's army guerillas opened fire on a military jeep on the central island of bohol. a constabularly captain was wounded in addition to the two fatalities
in another report, the military said three communist rebels and six moslem guerrillas were killed in earlier clashes in cagayan and on the southern island of mindanao
maj. v.g. jalligao said at least 50 new people's army guerrillas stormed the matilde olivas hospital late wednesday in cagayan province. jalligao said one civilian was wounded in the raid, after which the rebels fled toward a mountain village with medicine, food and other supplies
in mindanao's lanao del sur province, troops from the army's 35th infantry battalion came upon 20 moslem rebels of the moro national liberation front during a patrol friday and killed six of them in the ensuing gun battle. the remaining rebels fled, the military said
the clash occurred on the day president corazon aquino traveled to mindanao and the largely moslem island province of tawi-tawi to unveil economic development programs
during a speech in zamboanga city, mrs. aquino warned moslem countries against encouraging violence by the moslem rebel group, which has been waging a 16-year insurgency for a separate state in the south
fighting in the moslem insurgency peaked in the mid-1970s after the war had claimed more than 50,000 lives
