a man who was six months old when his parents divorced 40 years ago has been reunited with his father in the pinellas county jail
there were little tears in his eyes,'' sheriff gerry coleman said of inmate james stewart gaston. ``he was very affectionate toward his son.''
gaston has been jailed for brief stays more than 1,400 times because of alcohol-related misdemeanors. his son, james stewart gallagher of boston, learned his father was in the area from a friend in tampa who read about gaston in the newspaper
gaston, 65, was jailed tuesday for 10 days for violating an open alcohol container law
i've known him 30 years,'' the sheriff said. ``he probably was my first arrest. when he's sober, he's the nicest man you've ever met.''
gallagher, father of two young children, arrived thursday and coleman arranged a 24-hour furlough for gaston
